festival.introText:
Illusive Festival is delighted to invite everybody back for their eighth glorious year at Deene Park, Corby.

 

With huge smiles, warm hearts and open arms, they have been working non-stop, around the clock, determined to bring you what is promising to be the best year of Illusive yet.

 

From new stages, including a brand new Illuminaughty stage, new surprises, new traders and new performers, they really have pulled out every possible stop for Illusive’s most important and magical ingredient; you.

faqs.question: When is Illusive Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Illusive Festival is from Friday the 8th September - Monday 11th September 2023.

faqs.question: Travel information
faqs.answer:
Please use the main entrance which is off the A43.

The full site address is below but please adhere to the gate opening times for the event to avoid disappointment.

Deene Park

Deene

Corby

Northamptonshire

NN17 3EW

faqs.question: Does Illusive Festival have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: Yes, Illusive Festival is a camping festival

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Where is Illusive Festival?
faqs.answer: Illusive Festival is in Deene Park, Corby, North Northamptonshire NN17 3EG

faqs.question: Info on Campervans/ Caravans/ Vans
faqs.answer:
You will need to purchase a separate pass to allow the parking of your live-in vehicle at the vent. wans will be allowed in the campervan area, cars are also permitted for sleeping in. as long as you purchase a campervan pass.

trailer tents/wheeled tents are not allowed to be in standard public tent areas and will also require a campervan pass. oversized vehicles and Awnings will require two campervan passes to be purchased.

no power available in the campervan fields and generators are not allowed.

A TAXI COSTS APPROXIMATELY £12.00. THERE IS A DESIGNATED TAXI RANK NEAR THE ENTRANCE TO THE TICKET OFFICE FOR TAXI DROP OFFS AND COLLECTIONS.

faqs.question: Does Illusive Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer:
There is no children’s area at Illusive Festival and there is no Family Camping either. There are no persons under the age of 18 allowed on site at any point and this will be strictly enforced.

 

The bars will ask for ID for anyone who looks under 25. Acceptable forms of ID are:

 

Current Full or Provisional photo card driving licence

Current valid Passport (with photo)

UK ID Cards bearing the PASS Scheme hologram www.pass-scheme.org.u

faqs.question: by public transport
faqs.answer: PUBLIC TRANSPORT THE SITE IS LOCATED REASONABLY CLOSE TO BOTH CORBY TRAIN AND BUS STATIONS
